===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|衣|alt1=衤|旦|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=clothes}}. The original form is {{zh-m|*但}}, a {{Han compound|人|旦|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=person|nocap=1}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=但-original,襢}}

{{unc|zh}}. {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} gives several possibilities:
* Related to {{och-l|但|only}} ({{zh-ref|Pulleyblank, 1991c}});
* Related to {{och-l|丹|cinnabar; red}}, as skin colour is often associated with "red" ({{zh-ref|Lau, 1999}});
* Related to {{cog|bo|སྟར||to clean; to polish}}.

Differentiated into {{och-l|𢅒|{{q|of clothes}} to be left wide open}}.

